<body>
<bookmark branch="index" id="bm_id3155511"><bookmark_value>DATEDIF function</bookmark_value>
</bookmark>
<bookmark branch="hid/SC_HID_FUNC_DATEDIF" id="bm_id3149022" localize="false"/>
<h1 id="hd_id3155511"><variable id="datedif"><link href="text/scalc/01/func_datedif.xhp">DATEDIF</link></variable></h1>
<description id="par_id3153551"><ahelp hid="HID_FUNC_DATEDIF">This function returns the number of whole days, months or years between Start date and End date.</ahelp></description>
<embed href="text/scalc/00/avail_release.xhp#3.6"/>
<embed href="text/scalc/01/ful_func.xhp#func_head_syntax"/>
<paragraph role="code" id="par_id531642776283977">DATEDIF(Start date; End date; Interval)</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3152815">
<emph>Start date</emph> is the date from when the calculation is carried out.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3155817">
<emph>End date</emph> is the date until the calculation is carried out. End date must be later, than Start date.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3153183">
<emph>Interval</emph> is a string that determines how the difference will be calculated. Possible values are "d", "m", "y", "ym", "md" or "yd" regardless of the current language settings.</paragraph>
<embed href="text/scalc/01/04060102.xhp#datenumberinfo"/>
<embed href="text/scalc/01/04060102.xhp#datenumberwarn"/>
<table id="tbl_id1342204">
<tablerow>
<tablecell>
<paragraph role="tablehead" id="par_id5735953">Value for "Interval"<comment>Do not translate the text values in this column below</comment></paragraph>
</tablecell>
<tablecell>
<paragraph role="tablehead" id="par_id8360850">Return value</paragraph>
</tablecell>
</tablerow>
<tablerow>
<tablecell>
<paragraph role="tablecontent" id="par_id9648731" localize="false">"d"</paragraph>
</tablecell>
<tablecell>
<paragraph role="tablecontent" id="par_id908841">Number of whole days between Start date and End date.</paragraph>
</tablecell>
</tablerow>
<tablerow>
<tablecell>
    <paragraph role="tablecontent" id="par_id8193914" localize="false">"m"</paragraph>
</tablecell>
<tablecell>
<paragraph role="tablecontent" id="par_id9841608">Number of whole months between Start date and End date.</paragraph>
</tablecell>
</tablerow>
<tablerow>
<tablecell>
    <paragraph role="tablecontent" id="par_id2701803" localize="false">"y"</paragraph>
</tablecell>
<tablecell>
<paragraph role="tablecontent" id="par_id2136295">Number of whole years between Start date and End date.</paragraph>
</tablecell>
</tablerow>
<tablerow>
<tablecell>
    <paragraph role="tablecontent" id="par_id9200109" localize="false">"ym"</paragraph>
</tablecell>
<tablecell>
<paragraph role="tablecontent" id="par_id4186223">Number of whole months when subtracting years from the difference of Start date and End date.</paragraph>
</tablecell>
</tablerow>
<tablerow>
<tablecell>
    <paragraph role="tablecontent" id="par_id5766472" localize="false">"md"</paragraph>
</tablecell>
<tablecell>
<paragraph role="tablecontent" id="par_id1491134">Number of whole days when subtracting years and months from the difference of Start date and End date.</paragraph>
</tablecell>
</tablerow>
<tablerow>
<tablecell>
    <paragraph role="tablecontent" id="par_id5866472" localize="false">"yd"</paragraph>
</tablecell>
<tablecell>
<paragraph role="tablecontent" id="par_id1591134">Number of whole days when subtracting years from the difference of Start date and End date.</paragraph>
</tablecell>
</tablerow>
</table>

<embed href="text/scalc/01/ful_func.xhp#func_head_example"/>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3152589">
Birthday calculation. A man was born on 1974-04-17. Today is 2012-06-13.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3252589"><item type="input">=DATEDIF("1974-04-17";"2012-06-13";"y")</item> yields 38.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id451535132395328"><item type="input">=DATEDIF("1974-04-17";"2012-06-13";"ym")</item> yields 1.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id611535132402642"><item type="input">=DATEDIF("1974-04-17";"2012-06-13";"md")</item> yields 27.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id511535132411940">So he is 38 years, 1 month and 27 days old.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3352589">
<item type="input">=DATEDIF(DATE(1974,4,17);"2012-06-13";"m")</item> yields 457, he has been living for 457 months.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3452589">
<item type="input">=DATEDIF("1974-04-17";"2012-06-13";"d")</item> yields 13937, he has been living for 13937 days.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3752589">
<item type="input">=DATEDIF("1974-04-17";DATE(2012;06;13);"yd")</item> yields 57, his birthday was 57 days ago.</paragraph>
<embed href="text/scalc/01/common_func.xhp#sectiontechinfo"/>
